Medical Database Application
Overview
A Python-based medical database system for managing patients, treatments, visits, and tests. Includes a GUI for easy interaction.

Features
Patient management
Treatment tracking
Visit records
Test management
User-friendly GUI
Uses SQLite (no server required)
Installation
Ensure Python 3.7+ is installed.
Create and activate a virtual environment:
Install dependencies (if any):
(If requirements.txt is missing, install Tkinter and use standard library)
Usage
Run the application:

Follow the GUI prompts to manage medical records.

Database
Uses SQLite (medicalDatabase.db)
Tables are auto-created if not present
File Structure
main.py: Entry point
gui.py: GUI logic
backend.py: Core functions
patient.py, treatment.py, visits.py, tests.py: Database modules
Troubleshooting
If database file is missing, it will be created automatically.
Ensure Python and Tkinter are installed.

